########################################
##### GLOBAL RULES FOR SHYARA WEBSITE ##
########################################

# Architecture
- Project MUST follow root structure:
  /backend, /frontend, /infrastructure, /docs
- Backend = NestJS (preferred) or Express + TS.
- Frontend = Next.js 14 App Router with TypeScript.
- Every module must follow a clean, modular structure.

# UI/UX
- Implement premium SaaS-level UI (Linear/Vercel style).
- Use Tailwind + ShadCN UI everywhere.
- Fluid typography via clamp().
- Responsive grid system; no fixed heights.
- Hero, sections, CTAs must auto-resize for all devices.
- Apply micro-animations on scroll and hover.

# Performance
- Use next/image.
- Optimize LCP and CLS.
- Lazy load heavy components.
- All pages SSR with caching/ISR.

# Code Quality
- TypeScript strict mode.
- ESLint + Prettier formatting.
- No unused imports.
- Reusable components only — never duplicate code.
- Use hooks for shared logic.
- Use environment variables for all API calls.

# Frontend Rules
- Folder structure partitioned into:
  /app/_components
  /app/_sections
  /app/_layouts
  /app/_lib
  /app/api (client wrappers)
- Pages:
  - Home
  - About
  - Services
  - Contact
  - Careers (optional)
- Do NOT implement sub-domain pages here.
- Each section must be reusable and isolated.

# Backend Rules
- Use DTOs + Schemas for validation.
- Modular architecture for each feature.
- Helmet, CORS, rate limiter must be enabled.
- Controller → Service → Repository pattern.
- All endpoints typed with interfaces.

# Responsiveness Requirements
- Cards stack under 768px.
- Navigation becomes mobile hamburger.
- Containers max-width: 1280px.
- Padding adjusts per breakpoint.
- Animations stay below 200ms.

# Developer Experience
- Detailed comments in complex areas.
- Keep code readable and split into smaller components.
- Follow consistent naming conventions.

